|WKBSYNTAX
======

|YKBhelp parasites|WKB
|YKBparasite|WKB

|WKBDESCRIPTION
===========

|YKOParasites are living healing bargains bought at |YKBThe Brood Apothecary|YKO
in DarkWind City. A parasite can be swallowed to live inside you for a finite
amount of online time. While it is alive, it can restore hit points, spell
points, or both during heartbeat pulses when you are depleted.

Only one parasite may live in you at a time. Parasites do not restore past
your maximum hit points or spell points, and do not last forever.
Their remaining time pauses while you are offline, but they do not survive
death.

Stronger parasites can carry serious costs. Depending on the parasite, these
may include reduced maximum hit points, reduced maximum spell points, spell
point appetite while regenerating, weaker damage output, or other combat
burdens. If a parasite needs spell points as appetite and you cannot pay the
full appetite, it becomes starved for that pulse and does not mend you.

|WKBCOMMANDS
========

  |YKBparasite|YKO
    Shows your active parasite, healing pulse, burden, appetite, starvation
    state, and remaining online time.

  |YKBswallow <parasite>|YKO
    Installs a parasite carrier you are holding, if you meet its requirements.

  |YKBeat <parasite>|YKO
    Also installs a parasite carrier you are holding.

  |YKBlist parasites|YKO
    Used inside The Brood Apothecary to see available parasites.

  |YKBdescribe parasite <number or name>|YKO
    Used inside The Brood Apothecary to inspect requirements, healing, cost,
    duration, appetite, and burdens before buying.

  |YKBpurge parasite|YKO
    Used inside The Brood Apothecary to pay for removal of your active
    parasite.

|WKBLOCATION
========

|YKOThe Brood Apothecary is south of Xenor Road near the DarkWind City shop
district. From the road, look for the narrow apothecary doorway.

See also: |YKBhelp brood apothecary|YKO, |YKBhelp economy apothecary|YKO,
